    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-12-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 26, 1888</date>.<lb/>(Received January
                        9, 1889.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 240.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received to-day your No. 140, of the 13th
                    instant, and in reply must acknowledge the oversight of not informing the
                    Department of the notification at this legation, on the 30th of October last,
                    that the ports of Jacmel and Port de Paix were decreed under blockade. Such
                    decree never took effect at Jacmel, which remains, as are all the other ports on
                    the southern coast of Hayti, viz, Miragoane, Petit Goane, Jeremie, Jacmel, and
                    Aux Cayes, open to foreign trade.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. W. Thompson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
